Package: NxtIRF
Title: User-friendly Intron Retention and Alternative Splicing analysis using the IRFinder engine
Version: 0.98.0
Date: 2020-11-07
Authors@R: c(person("Alex Chit Hei", "Wong", email="a.wong@centenary.org.au", role=c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
	person("William", "Ritchie", role=c("aut", "cph")),
	person("Dadi", "Gao", role=c("ctb")),
	person("Ulf", "Schmitz", role=c("ctb")))    
Description: NxtIRF is the next evolution for Intron Retention detection for RNA-seq 
    data. NxtIRF is now fully compatible with Windows and Mac as well as Linux. In addition
    to analysis of bam files aligned to the genome using a splice-aware aligner (e.g. STAR),
    NxtIRF provides convenient pipelines for downstream analysis and publication-ready
    visualisation.
